 in ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"vectors"},{"type":"text","text":" is 0, returns 0 and"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"does nothing."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On success, the number of bytes written to the stream is returned."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It is not an error if this is not the same as the requested size, as it","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"can happen e.g. on a partial I\/O error, or if there is not enough","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"storage in the stream. All writes block until at least one byte"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"is written or an error occurs; 0 is never returned (unless","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nVectors"},{"type":"text","text":" is 0 or the sum of all bytes in "},{"code":"vectors","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is 0)."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cancellable"},{"type":"text","text":" is not "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", then the operation can be cancelled by"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"triggering the cancellable object from another thread. If the operation"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"was cancelled, the error "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cancelled"},{"text":" will be returned. If an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"operation was partially finished when the operation was cancelled the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"partial result will be returned, without an error."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Some implementations of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_output_stream_writev()"},{"type":"text","text":" may have limitations on the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"aggregate buffer size, and will return "},{"code":"invalidArgument","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" if these"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"are exceeded. For example, when writing to a local file on UNIX platforms,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the aggregate buffer size must not exceed ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_MAXSSIZE"},{"type":"text","text":" bytes."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Tries to write the bytes contained in the "},{"code":"nVectors","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"vectors"},{"text":" into the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"stream. Will block during the operation.","type":"text"}],"references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO":{"type":"topic","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","title":"GIO","url":"\/documentation\/gio","role":"collection","kind":"symbol"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/CancellableProtocol":{"role":"symbol","title":"CancellableProtocol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"CancellableProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"CancellableProtocol"}],"abstract":[{"code":"GCancellable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" allows operations to be cancelled."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableProtocol","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/cancellableprotocol"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/OutputStreamProtocol":{"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/OutputStreamProtocol","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/outputstreamprotocol","abstract":[{"code":"GOutputStream","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is a base class for implementing streaming output."}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"OutputStreamProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"OutputStreamProtocol","fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"tex